<p><b>Vue.js</b> (commonly referred to as <b>Vue</b>; pronounced <span class="rt-commentedText nowrap"><span class="IPA nopopups noexcerpt"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/English" title="Help:IPA/English">/<span style="border-bottom:1px dotted"><span title="&#39;v&#39; in &#39;vie&#39;">v</span><span title="/j/: &#39;y&#39; in &#39;yes&#39;">j</span><span title="/uː/: &#39;oo&#39; in &#39;goose&#39;">uː</span></span>/</a></span></span>, like "view"<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>) is an <a href="/wiki/Open-source_software" title="Open-source software">open-source</a> <a href="/wiki/Model%E2%80%93view%E2%80%93viewmodel" title="Model–view–viewmodel">Model–view–viewmodel</a> <a href="/wiki/JavaScript_framework" title="JavaScript framework">JavaScript framework</a> for building <a href="/wiki/User_interface" title="User interface">user interfaces</a> and <a href="/wiki/Single-page_application" title="Single-page application">single-page applications</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-11" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-11">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> It was created by Evan You, and is maintained by him and the rest of the active core team members coming from various companies such as <a href="/wiki/Netlify" title="Netlify">Netlify</a> and <a href="/wiki/Netguru" title="Netguru">Netguru</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-12" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-12">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
